text: I am deeply saddened by the FBI’s failure to act on the intelligence relating to the tragedy in Parkland. I trust that Director Wray will correct agency protocols and take appropriate disciplinary actions. Congress will conduct the oversight needed to enhance public safety.
Keeping the students and their families at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in my thoughts and prayers as we await more information about the situation unfolding in Parkland.

Tonight I voted to keep the government open, fund Community Health Centers, and increase resources for our military.  My colleagues in the Senate have yet another opportunity to support our men and women in uniform by passing this bill to continue funding the government.

I look forward to working with @POTUS on rebuilding our military. We must support those in uniform who protect us. Today the House passed a bill funding our military, and I hope soon the Senate will follow suit so our military has the ability to plan long term again.

We must secure our border and make sure we are properly equipping those who protect it. Border security must be a priority in any immigration plan. We must make sure that all ports of entry, both land and sea, are secure to ensure those who want to do us harm do not get in. #SOTU
The Tax Cuts and Jobs Act gives Americans real tax relief.  Companies are investing in workers and workers are investing in the economy, making it easier for everyone to get ahead. #SOTU

Signed & delivered. @POTUS just signed the Tax Cuts & Jobs Act into law, providing a simplified tax code that lower taxes for Northeast Florida families and will create more jobs for Americans. Historic day!

Happy birthday @USNationalGuard! Although we celebrate the NG’s founding in MA in 1636, FL had the Florida Militia that dates back to 1565. This means Florida was home to the 1st NG! No matter the founding year, they are “Always Ready, Always There!” & we are thankful. @FLGuard

Proud to honor a great NE Floridian, Rutledge Pearson by co-sponsoring a bill w/ @RepAlLawsonJr, that renames the Kings Rd office after him. He was a great leader in the fight for civil rights & a role model for students. Glad to see this bill unanimously pass the House.
Proud of the @BartramTrail Bears and their hard work during the state championship. Great game!
Go Navy! Beat Army!
Tonight the House voted to go to conference with the Senate to discuss our differences on the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act. We’re one step closer to tax relief for Northeast Florida families.

I am encouraged that the Senate passed the much-needed tax relief bill. I look forward to negotiating with them to ensure tax reform focuses on middle-class families and spurs the creation of good jobs and economic growth.
Prayers for the missing sailors who were involved in the US Navy plane crash in the Philippine Sea. Our hearts are with their families.
I would also like to commend the brave citizen that assisted in resolving the attack & those who helped at the scene.
Devastated by the attack in Texas today. Our prayers are w/ the victims and families. Thank you to the first responders who acted quickly.
The @USDA announced Beaches Emergency Assistance received funds to bring farm to table foods to low-income communities in NE FL. Congrats!
Our prayers are with the victims & families of this act of terror in New York City. Thank you to all the first responders.
Thank you @POTUS for your commitment to fighting the opioid crisis. We must ensure vulnerable Americans have support to overcome addiction.
Proud to introduce the Veterans Armed for Success Act which will help our veterans transition into the civilian workforce. @RepAlLawsonJr
Mobile Office Hours this Friday @ Oceanway Community Center, 2-4pm. Staff available to help w/ federal agencies & post hurricane resources.
.@fema opened a disaster recovery center at the Johnson Family YMCA to help NE FL storm survivors. Opened from 8am-8pm this week.
This morning our hearts are with Las Vegas. Praying for the victims & families of those involved in this senseless attack.
September is Suicide Prevention Month. If you know someone in crisis call 1-800-273-8255. You are not alone.
Staff from my office will host office hours Wed. from 1-3pm at the Beaches Branch Library to assist with post-Irma federal agency needs.
Jacksonville is under a flash flood warning. If you live in Evacuation Zone A or B, or low-lying areas, move to higher ground.
.@JTAFLA is scheduling Connexion rides for those registered through 630-CITY to special needs shelters & for life sustaining medical trips.
Thank you @POTUS and @fema for issuing an emergency declaration for the State of Florida in preparation of Hurricane Irma.
Good luck to the @floridastate Seminoles in Atlanta tonight! Looking forward to a great game.
Saddened to hear about the USS John S McCain, prayers with the @USNavy sailors aboard the ship as search and rescue efforts continue.
Tomorrow in NE FL we will fly our flags at half staff to remember Sgt. Murray and his comrades. Thank you for your service & sacrifice.
Congrats to Community Loaves owner Meredith Corey-Disch on receiving a Women’s Leadership fellowship! Great small business in NE FL!
Today is Purple Heart Day, a day to give thanks to the heroes of the past and present. Thank you for your service and sacrifice!
Happy birthday to the @USCG! Thank you to the brave men and women of the Coast Guard for protecting the USA & our maritime borders.
Proud to vote today to continue the VA Choice program and to build a new VA clinic in Jax. Veterans in NE FL deserve the best care.
Looking forward to throwing the first pitch at the @JaxShrimp game tonight! Feels good to be back home in the First Coast.
The DHS Authorization Act helps fulfill our duty to keep citizens in FL04 & across the country safe.
Proud to vote for the historic DHS Authorization Act that passed today in the House that included two of my bills. @HouseHomeland
.@SenJohnMcCain has dedicated a lifetime of selfless service to America. Our thoughts and prayers are with him and his family.
Yesterday the @USNavy announced the USS Thomas Hudner will be moving to Mayport in April. Great news for our national security & for NE FL.
Tune in tonight to the @HouseVetAffairs hearing on the expanded GI bill, which includes my Julian Woods Yellow Ribbon Program Expansion Act.
Thanks to @DeptVetAffairs Dr. Thornton, Dr. Tenhula & Director Wisnieski for discussing the importance of mental health for our vets. (2/2)
Our military readiness depends on having a force that knows their country and the systems they depend on have their back. (1/2)
My prayers go out to the family of Marine Sgt. Joseph Murray of Jacksonville. His dedication to his family, faith & country is inspiring.
Tragic loss of life in yesterday's @USMC KC-130 crash in MS. Our thoughts and prayers go out to the Marines and their families.
Congratulations to @GatorsBB on their first College World Series Championship! Way to bring it home to the Sunshine State!
The @JTAFLA center is an example of great collaboration between local, state, & federal agencies. Historic day for NE FL transportation!
Wishing the brave men and women of the 125th Fighter Wing a safe deployment. Your courage & devotion are appreciated!
God's greatest blessing is being a father and grandfather. Happy Father's Day to all excellent dads!
Today, our thoughts and prayers are with the families who lost loved ones on the USS Fitzgerald. Their heroic efforts won't be forgotten.
Prayers for @SteveScalise, police, staff, and all involved in the senseless act of violence this morning.
Excited to have been appointed to the @HouseJudiciary committee! Grateful for the opportunity to support the rule of law across our nation.
Let us never forget the Pulse attack on 49 innocent lives, and vow to do all in our power to stop those responsible for radical terrorism.
Tomorrow at 9:00am we join Orlando & all Floridians to pause and share a moment of silence to honor the victims of the Pulse terror attack.
The senseless acts of violence in Orlando are heartbreaking. The NE FL community stands with you, offering support & prayers.
The average annual premium increase since Obamacare mandates & regulations is $2,928. We must do better, status quo is not an option.
This Memorial Day, a great way to honor the men and women who sacrificed so much for us is to pass bills to improve veterans' lives. (1/2)
On this day and every day, we honor the bravery, dedication, and sacrifices of our men and women in uniform. #ArmedForcesDay2017
Tune in to C-Span now for a #NationalPoliceWeek tribute where I'll be honoring officers, including fallen @NCSO_FL Deputy Eric Oliver.
.@THEPLAYERSChamp put on another world class event this year! Hats off to the players, staff, volunteers, and entire NE FL community.
Happy Mother's Day to my wonderful wife and all great moms. Thank you for the love, support, and guidance you give!
Proud to co-sponsor the bipartisan #PAWSAct that will provide increased access to service dogs for our veterans with PTSD.
I supported the Working Families Flexibility Act to end outdated regulations & give workers more freedom through greater paid leave.
Florida has 2.3 million small businesses and over 43% of FL employees work for a small business. #smallbusinessweek @SBDCatUNF
It’s National Small Business Week! Small businesses employ over 47% of employees in the private-sector in the U.S. #SmallBusinessWeek
Congresswoman Ileana @RosLehtinen is a true public servant. Thank you for your dedication to Floridians. Your leadership will be missed!
Thank you @POTUS for your commitment to improving accountability at the VA & ensuring our vets are getting the service they deserve.
On Holocaust Remembrance Day, we will never forget the 11 million victims, including 6 million Jews, of this horrific crime against humanity
I want to wish everyone a Happy Easter that is full of renewal, hope, and the joy of the risen Lord!
Congratulations to Judge Gorsuch on being confirmed as our nation's newest Supreme Court Justice.
I was proud to co-sponsor H.R. 299 to expand benefits to Blue Water Vietnam Veterans who were exposed to agent orange.
I condemn this atrocious attack on Syrians and continue to pray for those affected. (2/2)
This horrific attack and blatant use of chemical weapons to murder and harm innocent families & children in Syria is unacceptable. (1/2)
I appreciate @USNavy @USCG @CustomsBorder & @HouseHomeland joining me in the effort to stem the tide of illegal immigration at the border.
We continue to pray for all the families affected by the fire and the first responders who are working hard to keep everyone safe.
My staff and I are in contact with officials to ensure first responders, firefighters, & residents have all they need to stay safe & secure.
Those near the fire should listen to all warnings and evacuation orders.

Thank you @NCSO_FL, @JSOPIO, @NassauEM @Nassau310, 
@IAFF3101, @FLForestService for working tirelessly to keep Nassau County residents safe.
West Nassau Airforce JROTC FL955 accomplished great things in '16 - 5,084 service hrs, 15 holiday food baskets & much more. Congratulations!
Successful Florida Ports Caucus meeting w/ bipartisan support of transportation & infrastructure. Working together for FL jobs! @JAXPORT
Thank you President John Delaney for your service & leadership to @UofNorthFlorida students. Looking forward to your future accomplishments.
I am very pleased with the Navy’s decision, which will enhance our national security by helping carry out important maritime missions.
Enjoyed discussing the future of @fema. Public safety, security, & preparedness are a priority in NE FL. @HouseHomeland
Congratulations to David Shulkin on your confirmation as Secretary of @DeptVetAffairs! Looking forward to working with you to repair the VA.
Proud to co-sponsor the #WINGMANAct that cuts red-tape & allows congressional staff to efficiently serve our veterans. @RepTedYoho
Congratulations @RepTomPrice on your confirmation as @HHSgov Secretary. Looking forward to working together to repeal & replace Obamacare.
